A Precept is a general rule, tenet or doctrine intended to regulate behaviour or thought.

The Precept Bible is based on the understanding of the scripture in Isaiah 28:9-10 where it clearly states how scriptures will be taught in the last days. The children of the promise would have forgotten their heritage and identity and all the history that they ought to have known.

They would now require some extensive hand-holding as they are taken from passage to passage, and the understanding of each line of scripture is ellucidated and taught to them precept by precept.

If you want to understand the bible, you will need to be guided by the precepts, which are the keys to unlocking the meanings and intents of its passages in context. Let scripture interpret scripture.

START LEARNING PRECEPTS NOW!
- Start by reading the verses and passages related to each precept;
- Get the understanding of the precept by reading the cross-linked verses;
- You begin to see the consistency in scripture when you realise that certain words and phrases maintain specific meaning in all the verses they appear in;
- Connect the dots and you begin to see the bigger picture of what the bible is really revealing.

MORE FEATURES WITH EACH UPDATE
- Easy navigation for chapters and verses;
- Quickly check up on precepts listed under a verse, and link to cross-linked verses;
- Adjust font sizes for accessibility;
- Use the contact form to send us messages and what you've discovered;
- Join our mailing list and get updates about our occasional updates and learning aids;

REDISCOVER THE CORRECT WAY TO UNDERSTAND SCRIPTURE
- Build up entire teaching series using bible precepts to maintain true scriptural meanings and consistency in the understanding delivered.

